gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for Highways Features: United States, 2011

gmx:scope.gco:CharacterString: Highways; Roads; National Highway System; Transportation corridors

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: State FIPS Code *this field is numeric*
An alphanumeric route identifier that is part of the State's LRS and used to identify locations along the State's roadway network.
The degree of access control for a given section of road.
County FIPS Code (3 digit). Can be combined with STFIPS to obtain 5-digit County FIPS C
the functional system upon which the section is located.
Urban Principal Arterial - Other Freeways and Expressways
This item is used to determine whether a roadway or structure is a one- or two-way operation
Maximum number of lanes in both directions designated for HOV operations.

A statistic used to estimate the amount of roughness in a measured longitudinal profile. The IRI is computed from a single longitudinal profile using a quarter-car simulation as described in the report "On the Calculation of IRI from Longitudinal Road Profile" (Sayers, M.W., Transportation Research Board 1501, Transportation Research Board, Washington, DC 1995).
Indicates whether the section is on the National Highway System (NHS) or is an NHS connector to an intermodal facility.
The entity that has legal ownership of a roadway.
Alphanumeric value for the signed route number shown on the marker described in the attributes SIGNING and QUALIFIER.
The value which best represents the manner in which the highway segment is signed on the route marker described in the SIGNING attribute
No Qualifier or Not Signed or Not Applicable
The value which best represents the manner in which the highway segment is signed with route markers.
Parkway Marker or Forest Route Marker
Roadway section that is a component of the Strategic Highway Network (STRAHNET).
Roadway section that is entirely on a bridge, tunnel or causeway.
Identifies sections that are toll facilities regardless of whether or not a toll is charged.
Indicates the presence of special tolls (i.e., High Occupancy Toll (HOT) lane(s) or other managed lanes).
The numeric urbanized area code for sections within an urbanized area boundary when the RUR_URB attribute is coded "3" or "4".
